comments.message:
This can be confusing with "encode_pldm_header_only", i think it was meant for commands with no request data. You can follow the template like in other functions. Sample example below

	struct pldm_header_info header = {0};
	header.instance = instance_id;
	header.msg_type = PLDM_REQUEST;
	header.pldm_type = PLDM_FRU;
	header.command = PLDM_GET_FRU_RECORD_TABLE_METADATA;
	int rc = pack_pldm_header(&header, &(msg->hdr));
	if (PLDM_SUCCESS != rc) {
		return rc;
	}
